          "input": {
            "command": "git add src/textual_xacts.cc && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nInclude virtual postings in balance assertions when no real posts exist\n\nBalance assertions on real postings used real_only=true unconditionally\n(from fix for #543), meaning they only examined real (non-virtual) posts\nwhen comparing against the asserted value.  This broke the pattern of\nsetting up an account with a virtual balance assignment and then\nasserting the combined balance with a real posting.\n\nThe fix: for a real posting, scan the account's prior post list.  If\nany prior real post exists, keep real_only=true (preserving the #543\nsemantics for mixed real/virtual accounts like budget envelopes).  If\nall prior posts are virtual, fall back to real_only=false so the\nassertion checks the combined total, matching what `ledger bal` shows.\n\nThe same real_only flag now also governs which same-transaction posts\nare subtracted during the diff computation, keeping the two halves of\nthe calculation consistent.\n\nFixes #1699\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"",
